HEADWORD: Brookite
<hw>Brook"ite</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Named from the
English mineralogist, H. J. <etsep>Brooke</etsep>.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral consisting of titanic oxide, and hence
identical with rutile and octahedrite in composition, but crystallizing
in the orthorhombic system.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brooklet</ent>⟦br⟧
